15009.name: rkr AlienWah
15009.desc: This effect features two alternating comb filters for a vocal/formant-like wah sound. It could be considered a combined flanger and phaser. It can be extreme or add very subtle shimmer

15005.name: rkr Analog Phaser
15005.desc: A physically-informed, highly-configurable digital model of an analog FET phaser effect.

15020.name: rkr Arpie
15020.desc: A pitch shifter that changes the shifting amount in a rhythmic pattern. Adds pulse and brightness to your sound.

15012.name: rkr Cabinet
15012.desc: Equalizer with preset curves to match the effect of various guitar cabinets.

15004.name: rkr Flanger/Chorus
15004.desc: A flanger or chorus (depending on delay time) effect. Allows for fractional delays for a more intense effect.

15027.name: rkr Coil Crafter
15027.desc: A equalizer that makes your pickups sound like different pickups. Can switch a strat to sound like humbuckers in a strat etc.

15038.name: rkr CompBand
15038.desc: Multi-band compressor with 4 frequency bands and wet/dry mix control. Each band has individual ratio and threshold controls.

15001.name: rkr Compressor
15001.desc: A flexible compressor with optional soft knee and makeup gain.

15015.name: rkr Derelict
15015.desc: A very configurable waveshaping distortion module with resonance control of the filters for extra color.

15019.name: rkr DistBand
15019.desc: A multi-band distortion allowing different character distortion of different frequencies. It is a waveshaping distortion with a different waveshaper selectable for each band.

15002.name: rkr Distorsion
15002.desc: A flexible waveshaping distortion with 30 waveshapes to choose from.

15017.name: rkr Dual Flange
15017.desc: Two flange effects cascaded to create unique and more intense tones than available through a single flanger.

15003.name: rkr Echo
15003.desc: Configurable echo effect with a reverse echo feature.

15036.name: rkr Echotron
15036.desc: An extremely-configurable delay that allows up to 127 taps. Individual tap timing can be customized and loaded through text files. You can also have a custom filter on each tap. Several example files included.

15026.name: rkr Echoverse
15026.desc: Configurable echo designed to be stable for thick, in-your-face walls of sound.

15000.name: rkr EQ
15000.desc: 10 band graphical equalizer with resonance control.

15007.name: rkr Exciter
15007.desc: Harmonic exciter that allows you to adjust the volume of each of 10 harmonics.

15021.name: rkr Expander
15021.desc: Analog BJT modeled dynamic expander for subtler noise suppression than a gate typically offers. Can also be used for interesting evelope-triggered swell and fade effects.

15043.name: rkr NoiseGate
15043.desc: Based on Gate, Steve Harris LADSPA plugin.

15006.name: rkr Harmonizer (no midi)
15006.desc: Pitch shifter that harmonizes with your dry signal. This works best for monophonic sounds (a single note at a time). Also allows selection of root and chord for intelligent harmonies.

15041.name: rkr Infinity
15041.desc: This is the audio equivalent of a barber pole effect, with 8 filter bands continuously sweeping up or down. This has enough flexibility to create effects anywhere from subtle to insane.

15013.name: rkr Musical Delay
15013.desc: Dual delay with delay times selectable by tempo and note subdivision.

15025.name: rkr MuTroMojo
15025.desc: State variable filter with envelope or LFO modulation. Allows it to act like a mixable blend of highpass, lowpass or bandpass filter. Similar to a mutron III. Also useful for classic wah pedal emulation when wah parameter is controlled by an expression pedal.

15039.name: rkr OpticalTrem
15039.desc: An optical tremolo effect emulation such as often built into a guitar amplifier. This varies the signal volume through an LFO.

15008.name: rkr Pan
15008.desc: LFO controlled auto-panning/stereo tremelo effect. Useful to expand your stereo image.

15042.name: rkr Phaser
15042.desc: More mild digital phaser with exponential LFO sweep.

15035.name: rkr Reverbtron
15035.desc: Convolution-based reverb effect. IR samples can be converted to .rvb format and loaded into this effect for a less cpu-intensive convolution. Several files included.

15018.name: rkr Ring
15018.desc: A ring modulator with monophonic frequency recognition for synthesis.

15031.name: rkr Sequence
15031.desc: 8-step modulation sequencer. Each step is user-adjustable. Signal amplitude, filter cutoff frequency, or pitch shifting modulations available.

15028.name: rkr Shelf Boost
15028.desc: Low-shelf filter for simple control of your tone.

15032.name: rkr Shifter
15032.desc: Pitch shifter with easy controls for expression pedal controled whammy effects. Also has a mode for envelope based control.

15022.name: rkr Shuffle
15022.desc: Creates interesting spatial effects. Converts stereo signal to Mid/Side and applys a parametric four band EQ to M or S channel. Effect based on Stereo Shuffling paper by Michael Gerzon.

15037.name: rkr StereoHarmonizer (no midi)
15037.desc: Pitch shifter that harmonizes 2 voices with your dry signal. This works best for monophonic sounds (a single note at a time). This version has a detune for stereo chorus effects. Also allows selection of root and chord for intelligent harmonies.

15034.name: rkr StompBox:Fuzz
15034.desc: Physically-informed fuzz stompbox emulation. Based on several popular schematics, this is designed to capture the sound of an era more than emulate a specific model.

15033.name: rkr StompBox
15033.desc: Physically-informed distortion stompbox emulation with 8 different distortion-character modes. Intended to allow quick dialing-in to the tone you want.

15030.name: rkr Sustainer
15030.desc: A very simple, no-frills soft knee compressor good for making notes sustain. Brighter than the full Rakarrack Compressor.

15023.name: rkr Synthfilter
15023.desc: A filter like what can be found in synthesizers. Up to 12 lowpass + 12 highpass filters with resonance. Cutoff frequency is controllable by LFO or volume envelope.

15016.name: rkr Valve
15016.desc: Tube distortion emulation with extra distortion available.

15024.name: rkr VaryBand
15024.desc: Multi-band tremolo effect allowing 2 LFOs to modulate volume of any combination of 4 frequency bands.

15040.name: rkr Vibe
15040.desc: The UniVibe was intended as a rotating speaker emulation. It does a poor job of that, but in its own right became a popular phase-shifter effect. This version has optional feedback to achieve some additional tones.

15029.name: rkr Vocoder
15029.desc: 32 band vocoder. This type of effect is well known for creating robot-like voices in popular music. The input is divided into frequency bands and each band's volume is controlled by an auxiliary input's frequency curve such that the output signal is filtered to sound like the aux signal.

15014.name: rkr WahWah
15014.desc: Wah effect controllable by the input volume envelope or by LFO.

15200.name: MDA Bandisto
15200.desc: This plug is like MultiBand but uses 3 bands of clipping instead of compression.

15300.name: MDA BeatBox
15300.desc: Contains three samples (kick, snare and hat) designed to be triggered by incoming audio in three frequency ranges.  The default samples are based on the Roland CR-78.

15400.name: MDA Combo
15400.desc: This plug-in can sound quite subtle but comes alive when used on guitar with the drive turned up!

15500.name: MDA De-ess
15500.desc: Reduce excessive sibilants (/s/ /t/ /sh/ etc.) in vocals and speech.

15700.name: MDA Delay
15700.desc: Simple stereo delay with feedback tone control

15800.name: MDA Detune
15800.desc: A low-quality stereo pitch shifter for the sort of chorus and detune effects found on multi-effects hardware

15900.name: MDA Dither
15900.desc: When a waveform is rounded to the nearest 16 (or whatever)-bit value this causes distortion. Dither allows you to exchange this rough sounding signal-dependant distortion for a smooth background hiss.

16000.name: MDA DubDelay
16000.desc: Delay with feedback saturation and time/pitch modulation

16400.name: MDA Image
16400.desc: Stereo image adjustment and M-S matrix

16600.name: MDA Leslie
16600.desc: Rotary speaker simulator. No overdrive or speaker cabinet simulation is added - you may want to combine this plug-in with Combo.  For a much thicker sound try combining two Leslie plug-ins in series!

16800.name: MDA Loudness
16800.desc: Equal loudness contours for bass EQ and mix correction

16900.name: MDA MultiBand
16900.desc: Multi-band compressor with M-S processing modes

17000.name: MDA Overdrive
17000.desc: Soft distortion. Possible uses include adding body to drum loops, fuzz guitar, and that 'standing outside a nightclub' sound. This plug does not simulate valve distortion, and any attempt to process organ sounds through it will be extremely unrewarding!

17200.name: MDA RePsycho!
17200.desc: Drum loop pitch changer. Event-based pitch shifter

17300.name: MDA RezFilter
17300.desc: Resonant filter with LFO and envelope follower

17400.name: MDA RingMod
17400.desc: Simple ring modulator with sine-wave oscillator

17500.name: MDA RoundPan
17500.desc: 3D panner. Like all 3D processes the result depends on where you sit relative to the speakers, and mono compatibility is not guaranteed. This plug-in must be used in a stereo channel or bus!

17700.name: MDA Splitter
17700.desc: Frequency/level crossover for setting up dynamic processing. This plug-in can split a signal based on frequency or level, for example for producing dynamic effects where only loud drum hits are sent to a reverb. Other functions include a simple "spectral gate" in INVERSE mode and a conventional gate and filter for separating drum sounds in NORMAL mode.

17900.name: MDA SubSynth
17900.desc:
Several low frequency enhancement methods. More bass than you could ever need!

Be aware that you may be adding low frequency content outside the range of your monitor speakers.  To avoid clipping, follow with a limiter plug-in (this can also give some giant hip-hop drum sounds!).

18100.name: MDA TestTone
18100.desc: Signal generator with pink and white noise, impulses and sweeps

18200.name: MDA ThruZero
18200.desc: Classic tape-flanging simulation. This plug simulates tape-flanging, where two copies of a signal cancel out completely as the tapes pass each other. It can also be used for other modulated delay effects such as phasing and simple chorusing.

18300.name: MDA Tracker
18300.desc: Pitch tracking oscillator, or pitch tracking EQ

18500.name: MDA VocInput
18500.desc: Pitch tracking oscillator for generating vocoder carrier input

18600.name: MDA Vocoder
18600.desc: Switchable 8 or 16 band vocoder. 16-band vocoder for applying the spectrum of one sound (the modulator, usually a voice or rhythm part) to the waveform of another (the carrier, usually a synth pad or sawtooth wave).

18700.name: Gx_AxisFace_
18700.desc: Simulation of the Classic Silicon Pedal

18800.name: Gx_bajatubedriver_
18800.desc: Tube based overdrive pedal simulation Based on the BaJaTubeDriver

18900.name: GxBlueAmp
18900.desc: Single - ended head amplifier simulation inspired by late 1950s amplifier designs, it delivers tight bass, clean mids and highs

19000.name: Gx_boobtube_
19000.desc: The BoobTube is a little tube boost pedal simulation. It adds some overdrive and tube compression along with boosting the signal

19100.name: GxBottleRocket
19100.desc: Analogue simulation of a tube preamp based on a classic tube overdrive

19200.name: GxClubDrive
19200.desc: Overdrive Pedal Simulation based on a EF86 Pentode Valve Simulation.

19300.name: Gx_CreamMachine_
19300.desc: Simulation, based on a tube power amp circuit

19400.name: GxDOP270
19400.desc: Based on a classic Overdrive Amp

19500.name: GxEpic
19500.desc: Simulation of a class A electric guitar valve amplifier

19600.name: GxEternity
19600.desc: This low compression overdrive pedal is perfect for any style of music that requires natural sounding overdrive

20000.name: GxHeathkit
20000.desc: Distortion Booster Pedal simulation based on a classic distortion/booster/fuzz

20100.name: GxHotBox
20100.desc: Analouge simulation of a tube preamp with overdrive and interactive tone control

20300.name: GxKnightFuzz
20300.desc: Vintage Fuzz Pedal simulation. This is a really nasty Fuzz Pedal, which act at lower/ moderate settings as a ultra dark fuzz, when settings get cranked up, it becomes more and more high harmonics.

20400.name: Gx_liquiddrive_
20400.desc: Liquid Drive provides a tonal response with a warm mild to aggressive overdrive, which can do anything from Blues to Hard Rock

20600.name: Gx_MicroAmp_
20600.desc: The MicroAmp is designed to be a transparent clean volume booster.

20800.name: Gx_quack_
20800.desc: Envelope controlled wah pedal with some extra features

21400.name: Gx_slowgear_
21400.desc: Attack-smoothing, auto-swelling pedal of the early 80s

21500.name: GxSunFace
21500.desc: A classic fuzz face with some light modifications

21600.name: Gx_sfp_
21600.desc: Analog simulation of a Fuzz pedal as LV2 plugin. In this simulation the trim pot, which is usualy in the housing, is exposed as control parameter. It adjust the amount of harmonics.

21800.name: Gx_vstb_
21800.desc: Analog simulation of a Tone Bender pedal as LV2 plugin
